Single lines
Type - Indicates the type of input control and for text input control it will be set to text
name - Used to give a name to the control which is sent to the server to be recognized and get the value(initial default value)
value - This can be used to provide an initial value inside the control
size - Allows to specify the width of the text-input control in terms of characters
maxlength - Allows to specify the maximum number of characters......


Label function - easy to modifiy 

<html>
	<head>
		<title>
			HTML Controls
		</title>
	</head>
	<body>
		
		<form>
		First name: <input type = "text" name="first_name" value="Enter name" size=70 maxlength=12 />
		<br>
		Last name: <input type = "text" name="last_name" value="Enter surname" size=40 maxlength=10/>
		<br><br><br>
		Username: <input type = "text" name="first_name" value="Enter name" size=70 maxlength=22 />
		<br>
		Password: <input type = "password" name="pass" value="EnterEnterEnter" size=40 maxlength=10>
		<br><br><br>
		<label for="fname">First name</label><br>
		<input type="text" id="fname" name="Jone"><br>
		<label for="fname">Last name</label><br>
		<input type="text" id="fname" name="Doe"><br>
		<br>
		<form>
			<fieldset>
			<legend>
			Personnel info
			</legend>
				<label for="fname">First name</label><br>
				<input type="text" id="fname" name="fname" value="Jone"><br>
				<label for="lname">Last name</label><br>
				<input type="text" id="lname" name="lname" value="Doe"><br><br>
			</fieldset>
		</form>
		<form>
		Click and choose from list combobox below<br>
			<input list="browsers" size=40>
			<datalist id="browsers">
				<option value="Internet Explorer">
				<option value="Firefox">
				<option value="Chrome">
				<option value="Opera">
				<option value="Safari">
			</datalist>
		</form>
	</body>
</html>
